he eTendersNI platform the works were awarded to Forrme Ltd and were due to have been completed in September 2019. Due to factors beyond THA's control, Forrme was unable to complete the works so THA now needs them to be completed urgently.</P><P>THA considers that it is entitled to award the works to Kelly Brothers Building Contractors LLP in accordance with Regulation 72(1)(c) of the Public Contract Regulations 2015, which allows contracting authorities to modify an existing contract without a new procurement procedure.</P></SHORT_DESCR><VAL_TOTAL CURRENCY="GBP">1250000.00</VAL_TOTAL><NO_LOT_DIVISION/><OBJECT_DESCR ITEM="1"><CPV_ADDITIONAL><CPV_CODE CODE="45232423"/><CPV_SUPPLEMENTARY_CODE CODE="IA01"/></CPV_ADDITIONAL><CPV_ADDITIONAL><CPV_CODE CODE="45233226"/></CPV_ADDITIONAL><CPV_ADDITIONAL><CPV_CODE CODE="44621000"/><CPV_SUPPLEMENTARY_CODE CODE="IA07"/></CPV_ADDITIONAL><n2016:NUTS CODE="UKN07"/><MAIN_SITE><P>Ardmore Hill Phase 2A, Ardmore Hill, Armagh, Co. Armagh BT60 1AA.</P></MAIN_SITE><SHORT_DESCR><P>Completion of 23 dwellings and related infrastructure (including a sewage pumping station, drains, access road, fencing, landscaping, utility connections and commissioning of mechanical and electrical installations). The contractor must also design the sewage pumping station and some other elements of the work.</P></SHORT_DESCR><DIRECTIVE_2014_23_EU><AC><AC_CRITERION>A supplier with the requisite skills and experience who can be appointed at short notice to meet the timetable for provision of social housing</AC_CRITERION><AC_CRITERION>Price</AC_CRITERION></AC></DIRECTIVE_2014_23_EU><NO_OPTIONS/><NO_EU_PROGR_RELATED/></OBJECT_DESCR></OBJECT_CONTRACT><PROCEDURE><DIRECTIVE_2014_23_EU><PT_AWARD_CONTRACT_WITHOUT_CALL><D_OUTSIDE_SCOPE/><D_JUSTIFICATION><P>After a competitive procurement exercise (advertised through the eTendersNI platform on 30 May 2017, reference CfT 965262) Triangle Housing Association Ltd (‘THA’) awarded the contract to Forrme Ltd.</P><P>Due to factors beyond THA's control, the contract cannot be completed by Forrme.</P><P>THA is committed to the provision of social housing and urgently requires completion of this development so it intends to enter into a contract with Kelly Brothers Building Contractors LLP no less than 10 days after publication of this notice. There will be no change in the intended scope of the works and similar contractual terms and conditions will apply.</P><P>THA considers that this course of action is compatible with Reg 72(1)(c) of the Public Contract Regulations 2015.</P><P>The statutory housing authority for Northern Ireland confirms that:</P><P>— housing need in the Borough of Armagh City, Banbridge and Craigavon remained at a consistently high level between 2014 and 2019,</P><P>— in March 2019 3 076 households were waiting for social rented housing and 1 719 of these were in housing stress,</P><P>— by comparison, only 557 households were accommodated in social rented housing in 2018-2019,</P><P>— the Borough needs another 360 social rented dwellings between 2018 and 2023.</P><P>THA's development at Ardmore Hill Phase 2A will provide 23 new homes for social renting in the city of Armagh. 3 of these homes have been specially designed to suit named households with a disabled family member.</P></D_JUSTIFICATION></PT_AWARD_CONTRACT_WITHOUT_CALL></DIRECTIVE_2014_23_EU><NO_CONTRACT_COVERED_GPA/></PROCEDURE><AWARD_CONTRACT ITEM="1"><TITLE><P>Ardmore Hill Phase 2A, Armagh</P></TITLE><AWARDED_CONTRACT><DATE_CONCLUSION_CONTRACT>2019-12-06</DATE_CONCLUSION_CONTRACT><CONTRACTORS><NO_AWARDED_TO_GROUP/><CONTRACTOR><ADDRESS_CONTRACTOR><OFFICIALNAME>Kelly Brothers Building Contractors LLP</OFFICIALNAME><ADDRESS>Milltown East Industrial Estate, Upper Dromore Road</ADDRESS><TOWN>Warrenpoint</TOWN><POSTAL_CODE>BT34 3PN</POSTAL_CODE><COUNTRY VALUE="UK"/><PHONE>+44 2841752502</PHONE><E_MAIL>enquiries@kellybrothers.co.uk</E_MAIL><FAX>+44 2841752008</FAX><n2016:NUTS CODE="UKN08"/><URL>http://kellybrothers.co.uk</URL></ADDRESS_CONTRACTOR><SME/></CONTRACTOR></CONTRACTORS><VALUES><VAL_TOTAL CURRENCY="GBP">1250000.00</VAL_TOTAL></VALUES><LIKELY_SUBCONTRACTED/><PCT_SUBCONTRACTING>75</PCT_SUBCONTRACTING><INFO_ADD_SUBCONTRACTING><P>Design and construction of the sewage pumping station</P><P>Electrical work</P><P>Plumbing work</P><P>Landscaping</P></INFO_ADD_SUBCONTRACTING></AWARDED_CONTRACT></AWARD_CONTRACT><COMPLEMENTARY_INFO><ADDRESS_REVIEW_BODY><OFFICIALNAME>The Royal Courts of Justice</OFFICIALNAME><TOWN>Belfast</TOWN><COUNTRY VALUE="UK"/></ADDRESS_REVIEW_BODY><DATE_DISPATCH_NOTICE>2019-12-06</DATE_DISPATCH_NOTICE></COMPLEMENTARY_INFO></F15_2014></FORM_SECTION></TED_EXPORT>